{% comment %}
  snippets/product-carousel.liquid
  [1.2.1 → 1.1.2] In-feed horizontally scrolling product card carousel.

  Injected between product rows by collection-promo → promo-block.
  Always full row width. Source products come from block.settings.source_collection
  if set, otherwise falls back to the current collection.

  Parameters:
    block  {Object}  required — Shopify block with settings:
      heading           {String}     — carousel heading
      source_collection {collection} — optional; defaults to current collection

  Pitfall — variable scope in render tags:
    Shopify's `render` tag runs in an isolated scope. The `collection`
    variable from the parent is NOT available here. We resolve the
    source collection from the block setting and fall back to
    `collections[collection.handle]` passed via the block's own context.
    Because render is isolated, we pass collection_handle as a param
    from collection-promo if needed — but since block settings include
    a collection picker, we access it directly via block.settings.

  CSS: product-carousel.css
  JS:  product-carousel.js
{% endcomment %}

{{ 'product-carousel.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

{%- liquid
  assign pc_heading    = block.settings.heading | default: 'You might also like'
  assign pc_source     = block.settings.source_collection
  assign pc_products   = pc_source.products | default: empty
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  Pitfall: if source_collection is blank in the block settings,
  pc_source is nil and pc_products is empty. We cannot fall back to
  `collection` (out of scope in render). The merchant must set a
  source collection in the block settings, or we render nothing.
  Surface a theme-editor-only notice when no source is set.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- if pc_source == blank -%}
  {%- comment -%} Editor notice only — invisible on storefront {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="product-carousel product-carousel--empty" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
    <p class="product-carousel__notice">
      Select a source collection for this carousel in the theme editor.
    </p>
  </div>
{%- elsif pc_products != empty -%}

  <div class="product-carousel" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>

    {%- if pc_heading != blank -%}
      <h2 class="product-carousel__heading">{{ pc_heading }}</h2>
    {%- endif -%}

    <div class="product-carousel__track" data-product-carousel-track>
      {%- for product in pc_source.products limit: 12 -%}
        {%- render 'product-card', product: product, show_compare: false -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>

    <button
      class="product-carousel__btn product-carousel__btn--prev"
      type="button"
      aria-label="Previous"
      data-product-carousel-prev
    >
      <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M10 12L6 8l4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </button>
    <button
      class="product-carousel__btn product-carousel__btn--next"
      type="button"
      aria-label="Next"
      data-product-carousel-next
    >
      <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M6 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </button>

  </div>

{%- endif -%}

<script src="{{ 'product-carousel.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>